    "response": "To compute the **sample variance** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{1, 12, -17, -3, -11, -5\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the sample mean ($\\bar{x}$)\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{1 + 12 + (-17) + (-3) + (-11) + (-5)}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{1 + 12 - 17 - 3 - 11 - 5}{6} = \\frac{-19}{6}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Compute the squared differences from the mean\n\n$$\n(1 - (-\\frac{19}{6}))^2 = \\left(\\frac{25}{6}\\right)^2 = \\frac{625}{36}\n$$\n$$\n(12 - (-\\frac{19}{6}))^2 = \\left(\\frac{91}{6}\\right)^2 = \\frac{8281}{36}\n$$\n$$\n(-17 - (-\\frac{19}{6}))^2 = \\left(-\\frac{95}{6}\\right)^2 = \\frac{9025}{36}\n$$\n$$\n(-3 - (-\\frac{19}{6}))^2 = \\left(\\frac{11}{6}\\right)^2 = \\frac{121}{36}\n$$\n$$\n(-11 - (-\\frac{19}{6}))^2 = \\left(-\\frac{43}{6}\\right)^2 = \\frac{1849}{36}\n$$\n$$\n(-5 - (-\\frac{19}{6}))^2 = \\left(\\frac{9}{6}\\right)^2 = \\frac{81}{36}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared differences\n\n$$\n\\text{Sum of squares} = \\frac{625 + 8281 + 9025 + 121 + 1849 + 81}{36}\n$$\n\n$$\n\\text{Sum of squares} = \\frac{20002}{36}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 4: Divide by $n - 1$"
